    rationale: "The papillomacular bundle \u2014 the axons from the macula carrying color and fine detail information \u2014 runs centrally within the optic nerve and is particularly susceptible to demyelination and ischemia. Because color discrimination (especially red-green) depends on intact cone pathway transmission through these fibers, subtle optic nerve damage disrupts color vision before causing measurable acuity loss. This makes red-green color desaturation and Ishihara plate errors sensitive early signs of optic neuritis and other optic neuropathies. Color processing is not exclusively in the LGN, and cones are concentrated centrally (fovea), not peripherally.",
