    rationale: "Chronic Eustachian tube dysfunction creates persistent negative middle ear pressure, which progressively retracts the TM \u2014 particularly the pars flaccida (the weakest, most superior portion). This retraction pocket traps desquamated squamous epithelium (keratin), which accumulates and expands, forming a cholesteatoma. The mass is locally destructive, eroding ossicles, the tegmen, and the facial nerve canal. The sequence is: dysfunction \u2192 negative pressure \u2192 retraction \u2192 keratin accumulation \u2192 cholesteatoma. Positive pressure, ossicular erosion as a primary event, and bacterial superinfection are not the initiating mechanism.",
