    rationale: "Phenylephrine is a selective alpha-1 adrenergic agonist with a relatively shorter duration of action (~4 hours). Oxymetazoline is an imidazoline derivative that activates both alpha-1 and alpha-2 receptors, producing a longer duration of vasoconstriction (~8\u201312 hours). Both agents can be absorbed systemically through nasal mucosa and may cause transient hypertension, so neither is entirely free of systemic effects \u2014 making choice C incorrect. Oxymetazoline does not preferentially cause central hypertension via alpha-2 mechanisms in clinical nasal doses. Both agents are used in adults; oxymetazoline is not contraindicated in adults.",
